<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Wolves have secured the signing of Ki-Jana Hoever from Liverpool, their fifth deal of the summer transfer window.  </p>

<p>The Dutch centre-back made two appearances in the FA Cup for the Reds' first-team but never appeared in the Premier League, instead impressing for their under-23 side. </p>

<p>Wolves have already made a record signing this summer with Fabio Silva moving from Porto for £36m, also loaning Vitinha from the Portuguese club and bringing in Lyon's Marcal for £1.8m. </p>

<p>More to follow...  </p>

<p>Wolves have completed the signing of 18-year-old Liverpool defender Ki-Jana Hoever </p>

<p>The defender has been part of Jurgen Klopp's squad during a golden period at Anfield </p>
